<subSubSection lastPageId="147" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="147" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
Undershrub from a thickened woody rootstock to 60 cm with rigid (but not spiny) branches spreading widely at almost a right angle and forming an en 
<pageBreakToken pageId="147" pageNumber="148" start="start">twined</pageBreakToken>
mass; stems and leaves pubescent with spreading hairs. Leaves sessile, 0.5-5.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-0.9 cm, linear to oblong, acute, margin entire to undulate, pubescent, merging upwards into the bracts. Flowers pedunculate, solitary or in 2-3-flowered cymes; bracts 3-20 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-2.5 mm, suborbicular to broadly ovate; peduncles 0.8-5.5 cm, straight, rigid, usually arising at 90Â° to the stem; bracteoles 2-3 mm, filiform; pedicels 0-1 mm, often at an angle from the peduncle; outer sepals 4-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm, ovate, acute with mucronate apex, pilose, pubescent or, rarely, glabrous on the abaxial surface, sometimes glabrescent in fruit; inner sepals similar but less hairy and commonly convex; corolla 1.1-1.8 cm, white or purplish-flushed, somewhat undulate but not lobed, midpetaline bands pubescent; ovary glabrous to hirsute, style glabrous; style divided 5-6 mm above base; capsule glabrous or with a few apical hairs, seeds hirsute. [
<bibRefCitation author="Petrov, VA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="132 - 150" refId="B265" refString="Petrov, VA, 1935. Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium. Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique 44: 132 - 150" title="Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium." volume="44" year="1935">Petrov 1935</bibRefCitation>
: 138 (plate under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="V. Petrov" authorityYear="1935" baseAuthorityName="O. Kuntze" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus turcomanicus" order="Solanales" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="turcomanicus">
